modules.description: This module implements DNS client transport logic using non-blocking I/O over Lwt_unix sockets, supporting both plaintext and TLS connections. It manages connection state, sends and receives DNS messages, and handles timeouts and random number generation for DNS operations. Concrete use cases include initiating DNS queries over UDP or TCP with optional TLS, handling connection lifecycle events, and integrating with asynchronous networking stacks.

This module implements DNS client functionality over Lwt_unix with non-blocking I/O, supporting DNS queries via UDP, TCP, and TLS. It provides functions to resolve domain names to IPv4/IPv6 addresses, retrieve resource records, and handle raw DNS replies, with configurable timeouts, caching, and EDNS settings. Concrete use cases include asynchronous DNS resolution in networked applications and interacting with DNS servers using secure transports.
